The late Ontlametse Phalatse will be laid to rest tomorrow.Ontlametse&rsquo;s father, Lawrence Matjane has this morning confirmed that she will be laid to rest tomorrow in her hometown of Hebron.The service will commence at 7am tomorrow, followed by burial procedures at Herbron Cemetery.&nbsp;The ceremony will be attended by high profile dignitaries like president Jacob Zuma, who will be speaking at the funeral.Yesterday, Ontlametse was remembered in a dignified memorial service at Hebron, in the North West.The service was attended by her close family and friends as well as members of the media and other dignitaries.Ontlametse inspired many people across the country and her memorial service was testament to that legacy.Watch a video of the memorial service here: